stylometry: Our group project consisted of taking a company that was in the real business world currently. Sally Beauty Supply is a retail store for supplies, equipment and other beauty needs. The problem is with waiting lines for the customer. We decided we would use enough workers to have someone on the floor helping the customers and two others to run two registers. We chose to do a friday during the week at peek hours of 5-8pm (closing time). The problem we must prove is that one line and two registers is more efficient and better than two lines with two registers-( where customers in that line can only go to that register). Our factors to include were time a customer waits in line, how long it takes to process a customer (including manual ringing at each register), how many customers can be serviced within an hour, etc. By using M/M/s and M/M/1 templates we compared our results and ultimately found our conclusion to be that one line with two registers is the right solution.
